-- EBRD to Fund Ukraine’s Energy Efficiency Projects, Izvestia Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-07-03T07:04:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/ebrd-to-fund-ukraine-s-energy-efficiency-projects-izvestia-says.html
The European Bank for Reconstruction
and Development  may invest at least 100 million euros ($126
million) next year to improve the energy efficiency of apartment
buildings in  Ukraine ,  Ekonomicheskie Izvestia  reported, citing
EBRD’s senior project manager Sergiy Maslichenko.  The EBRD will provide financing after Ukraine reforms its
management system of the apartment buildings, according to the
newspaper. The cost of improving the external insulation
residential buildings in Ukraine may be as much as 30 billion
euros, Izvestia said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  